name: r-sfheaders
raw_meta_yaml:
{% set version = "0.4.0" %}
{% set posix = 'm2-' if win else '' %}
{% set native = 'm2w64-' if win else '' %}

package:
  name: r-sfheaders
  version: {{ version|replace("-", "_") }}

source:
  url:
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/sfheaders_{{ version }}.tar.gz
    - {{ cran_mirror }}/src/contrib/Archive/sfheaders/sfheaders_{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: 86bcd61018a0491fc8a1e7fb0422c918296287b82be299a79ccee8fcb515e045

build:
  merge_build_host: true  # [win]
  number: 0
  rpaths:
    - lib/R/lib/
    - lib/

requirements:
  build:
    - {{ compiler('c') }}              # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_c') }}        # [win]
    - {{ compiler('cxx') }}            # [not win]
    - {{ compiler('m2w64_cxx') }}      # [win]
    - {{ posix }}filesystem        # [win]
    - {{ posix }}make
    - {{ posix }}sed               # [win]
    - {{ posix }}coreutils         # [win]
    - {{ posix }}zip               # [win]
  host:
    - r-base
    - r-rcpp
    - r-geometries
  run:
    - r-base
    - {{ native }}gcc-libs         # [win]
    - r-rcpp
    - r-geometries

test:
  commands:
    - $R -e "library('sfheaders')"           # [not win]
    - "\"%R%\" -e \"library('sfheaders')\""  # [win]

about:
  home: https://dcooley.github.io/sfheaders/
  license: MIT
  summary: Converts between R and Simple Feature 'sf' objects, without depending on the Simple Feature library. Conversion functions are available at both the R level, and through 'Rcpp'.
  license_family: MIT
  license_file:
    - {{ environ["PREFIX"] }}/lib/R/share/licenses/MIT
    - LICENSE

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - conda-forge/r
